Jum'at, 03 Muharrom 1445 H/ 21 Juli 2023 M. Dilaksanakan rapat persiapan Imtihan Dauri 1 (IMDA) tingkatan Sifir, Ibtidaiyah dan Tsanawiyah. Bertempat di aula madrasah PP. Raudlatul Muta'allimin Ombul Sari.

Berjalannya rapat persiapan IMDA 1 kali ini dihadiri oleh  jajaran asatidz dan asatidzah dari masing masing tingkatan, yang dipimpin langsung oleh K. Amin Nasir selaku pengasuh PP. Raudlatul Muta'allimin Ombul sari, Tlambah, Karangpenang, Sampang.

Semoga pelaksanaan Imda 1 ini berjalan dengan lancar, dan para peserta mendapatkan nilai yang diharapkan. Aamiin ya robbal 'alamin.

"Making Aliyah was not a decision fueled by a single 'Aha! moment'; rather, it entailed a careful evaluation of various factors, including family, career, personal identity, responsibilities, and life stage. 

Ultimately, the driving force behind this life-changing move was a profound belief that the future of the Jewish people, physically, religiously, and culturally, resided in Israel. The journey came with its share of challenges, from communication and navigating the unfamiliar landscape to finding a sense of belonging. However, through perseverance and the invaluable support from organizations like Nefesh B'Nefesh, these obstacles were gradually overcome. 

This transformative experience inspired me to write a book, 'This Year in Jerusalem! Aliyah Dispatches' with a preface written by NBN Co-Founder and Executive Director, Rabbi Yehoshua Fass. Visiting a place is pleasant, but things look different when you're actually living there. Once Israeli, I found myself flooded with impressions. When family and friends with whom I shared them responded with interest, I just kept going, and so did the flood of impressions became this book.

I hope the book conveys the message that Aliyah is a continual process, one that demands time, effort, and adaptability but is undeniably rewarding and completely worth it.

The book is filled with 'Only in Israel' moments, but one that comes to mind is how clerks in medical clinics who check you in and draw your blood look at you with serious concern, as though they are your aunt, and then wish you a Refuah Shlemah.

To those on the fence about making Aliyah, my advice is to think deeply, but not to let overthinking stall the decision-making process – ultimately, the right time is for you to decide. Israel is an amazing place. It is also very different and very, very intense. Learning to adapt and appreciate is worth the effort."

- Avi Rockoff 

 Marco Jona

WORKSHOP AWAL TAHUN PELAJARAN DAN PERSIAPAN IMPLEMENTASI KURIKULUM MERDEKA 

Hari Kedua 
Kamis,06 Juli 2023 

Seluruh Staff Pengajar MTs YPPA Cipulus mengikuti kembali kegiatan  workshop .dimana di hari kedua ini seluruh peserta fokus mempersiapkan upaya Implementasi Kurikulum Merdeka yang langsung diarahkan oleh Pengawas Madrasah ,yaitu Ibu Drs.Hj.Widayanti,M.Pmat

Dimana, pada awal tahun ajaran 2023/2024 ini MTs YPPA CIPULUS akan siap mempergunakan Kurikulum Merdeka , dimulai dari jenjang kelas 7 .
Untuk mematangkan rencana tersebut, para pengajar MTs YPPA Cipulus fokus bahkan langsung mempersiapkan dan menggali lebih lagi  mengenai  kurikulum merdeka, yang sebelumnya sudah di sosialisasikan.

Para Peserta berkesempatan diarahkan langsung oleh  pengawas,terkait kurikulum merdeka, seperti :
- Menganalisis Capain Pembelajaran(CP) lalu bagaimana cara penyusunan Tujuan Pembelajaran(TP) dan ATP bahkan Modul ajar.
- Penyusunan Kurikulum Operasional Madrasah 
- Perencanaan  Profil Pelajar Pancasila dan Pelajar Rahmatanlillalamin(P5RA)
